description: Odd Molly International AB engages in the design, marketing, and sale of clothing and accessories for women. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm and currently employs 70 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2007-06-18. The firm specializes in the design, market and sale of female clothing and accessories, including shirts, pants, blouses, dresses, jackets, underwear, scarves, socks, and bags, among others. The company outsources production to independent suppliers, which are located in Asia and Europe. The firm distributes its collection via retail stores, shop-in-shops, outlets, external retailers, local agents, as well as via an online shop. The company operates worldwide in Sweden, Norway, Denmark, Germany, Switzerland, the United States, Japan, and Australia, among others. Furthermore, the Company controls two wholly owned subsidiaries: Odd Molly Inc and Odd Molly Denmark ApS.
